 In K2K, a beam of muon neutrinos were directed from the 12 GeV proton synchotro
n at KEK to the Kamioka Observatory at a distance of 250 km.
 While travelling through the Earth, the neutrinos oscillate before they
 are observed at Kamioka.
 Prior to K2K, neutrino sources included the atmosphere, the Sun, and one
 supernova.
\end_layout

